               <head>'Ishrat kadah-yi afaq of Chandu La'l Shadan</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿIshrat kadah-'i āfāq by Chandū Laʿl "Shādān"</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084 http://lccn.loc.gov/no99087640 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/n82048874 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh96008179" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4386-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657199.0x000001 viaf_37804758">Chandū Laʿl "Shādān"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657199.0x000001 viaf_37804758">چندو لعل شادان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22009">ʿIshrat kadah-'i āfāq</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22009">عشرۃ كدهٔ آفاق</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Work of mixed prose and verse by Mahārājah Chandū Laʿl bearing the takhalluṣ "Shādān", connecting his family's history with the foundations of the Āṣafjāhī state and his patron, the Nizam of Hydrabad, Sikandar Jāh ibn Niẓām ʿAlī (d. 1244/1829), for whom he was prime minister </p>
                        <p>The work consists of 3 parts following a short preface: 1) historical and autobiographical material (beginning f. 6r); 2) versified (beginning f. 41r); and 3) edifying tales (beginning f. 49r)</p>
                        <p>Ornamented beginning with ʿunvān</p>
                        <p>Note dated</p>
                        <p>Rare</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note />
                  </msItem>
